wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the CloudCanvas-TF project overview section. Explain the project's purpose as a visual infrastructure design studio that enables users to create Google Cloud Platform (GCP) infrastructure designs through drag-and-drop interface, automatically generating clean Terraform configurations. Document the target audience, key benefits, and use cases. Describe the technology stack including Angular 21, TypeScript, and modern web technologies. Explain how the visual design approach improves infrastructure as code workflows. Include both conceptual overviews for beginners unfamiliar with IaC and technical details for experienced developers. Use terminology consistent with the codebase and provide practical examples demonstrating the value proposition.

wiki_catalogs.name: GraphStateService
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive documentation for the GraphStateService, the central state management component of CloudCanvas-TF. Document the signal-based reactive state architecture, including state initialization, CRUD operations for infrastructure nodes and edges, and automatic dirty state tracking. Explain the canonical graph representation, node positioning, edge creation and validation, and state persistence mechanisms. Detail the reactive update patterns, subscription management, and state synchronization across components. Include practical examples of state mutations, batch operations, and state restoration. Document the service's role in coordinating with other core services like validation and terraform generation. Address performance considerations, memory management, and state consistency patterns.

wiki_catalogs.name: System Design Patterns
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create architectural documentation for CloudCanvas-TF's core design patterns. Detail the MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) pattern implementation through Angular components and signals-based state management. Explain the Plugin Pattern used for extensible GCP resource support, including the ResourcePlugin interface and dynamic plugin loading mechanisms. Document the Observer Pattern implementation through Angular Signals for reactive state updates. Cover the Factory Pattern used for dynamic resource plugin instantiation. Include the Canonical Data Model approach with InfraGraph as the single source of truth. Explain the separation of concerns between UI components, business logic services, and data models. Provide concrete examples from the codebase showing how these patterns work together to create a maintainable and extensible architecture.

wiki_catalogs.name: Canvas System
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive documentation for the Canvas System component. Document the canvas coordinate system, zoom and pan capabilities, and grid snapping behavior. Explain the integration with Angular CDK for drag-and-drop operations, mouse event handling for selection and manipulation, and real-time rendering of infrastructure graphs. Cover the canvas state management, viewport calculations, and responsive design considerations. Include practical examples of canvas interactions, custom styling options, and performance optimization techniques for large graphs.

Include practical examples of implementing custom plugins, defining resource schemas, and handling validation logic. Document the plugin contract benefits for extensibility and maintainability.

wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# CloudCanvas-TF: Visual Infrastructure Design Studio for Google Cloud

## Project Introduction

CloudCanvas-TF is a **visual infrastructure design studio** that enables developers to create Google Cloud Platform (GCP) infrastructure designs through an intuitive drag-and-drop interface, automatically generating clean, editable Terraform configurations. The project addresses the common pain points of Terraform complexity and cloud console clicking by providing a beginner-friendly visual approach while maintaining expert-level output quality.

### Purpose Statement
Enable anyone on a development team to model GCP infrastructure visually and produce reproducible Terraform that advanced users can still edit and commit to Git repositories.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Accelerate Infrastructure Design**: Visual composition lowers cognitive load compared to raw HCL for beginners
- **Maintain Code Quality**: Generate clean, deterministic Terraform output that experts can review and modify
- **Enhance Collaboration**: Provide team-friendly deliverables with diagnostics and architecture insights
- **Support Rapid Prototyping**: Enable quick cloud architecture drafts with built-in security and cost guidance

### Target Audience
1. **Application developers** with basic cloud knowledge but low Terraform confidence
2. **DevOps/platform engineers** who need rapid prototyping and team collaboration  
3. **Founders/startups** needing quick cloud architecture drafts with cost/safety guidance

## Technical Architecture

The application follows a modern Angular 21 architecture with a plugin-based design pattern, centered around a canonical InfraGraph data model. The system is structured as a single-page application with reactive state management using Angular Signals.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[App Component] --> B[Graph State Service]
    A --> C[Validation Service]
    A --> D[Terraform Generator Service]
    
    B --> E[Core Models]
    C --> F[Plugin Registry]
    D --> F
    
    F --> G[Resource Plugins]
    G --> H[Compute Network Plugin]
    G --> I[Compute Instance Plugin]
    G --> J[Storage Bucket Plugin]
    G --> K[Container Cluster Plugin]
    
    C --> L[Graph Engine Service]
    D --> M[AST Serializer]
    
    N[Canvas Component] --> B
    O[Inspector Component] --> B
    P[Palette Component] --> B
    Q[Diagnostics Component] --> B
    R[Code Preview Component] --> B
```

### Component Breakdown

The application is organized into distinct functional modules:

- **Core Layer**: Central state management and data models
- **UI Layer**: Visual components for canvas, palette, inspector, and diagnostics
- **Infrastructure Layer**: Plugin system for GCP resource modeling
- **Generation Layer**: Terraform code generation and validation engines
- **Persistence Layer**: Local storage and project management

### Design Patterns

1. **Plugin Architecture**: Each GCP resource type is encapsulated in a dedicated plugin
2. **Signals-Based State Management**: Reactive updates throughout the application
3. **Canonical Data Model**: Single source of truth for infrastructure graphs
4. **AST-First Generation**: Terraform generation uses structured blocks rather than string templates

### System Relationships

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as Canvas Component
    participant S as Graph State Service
    participant V as Validation Service
    participant T as Terraform Generator
    participant P as Plugin Registry
    
    U->>C: Drag resource to canvas
    C->>S: addNode()
    S->>V: validateAll()
    V->>P: getPlugin()
    V->>P: validate()
    P-->>V: Diagnostic[]
    V-->>S: Diagnostics
    S->>T: generate()
    T->>P: getPlugin()
    T->>P: toTerraform()
    P-->>T: Terraform Blocks
    T-->>S: Generated Files
    S-->>C: Update UI
```

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points

The application bootstraps through a standard Angular entry point:

- **Bootstrap**: `src/main.ts` - Initializes the Angular application
- **Root Component**: `src/app/layout/app.component.ts` - Orchestrates the entire UI layout
- **Configuration**: `angular.json` - Angular CLI build configuration
- **Package Management**: `package.json` - Dependencies and scripts

### Core Modules

**State Management**: `src/app/core/services/graph-state.service.ts`
- Centralized reactive state using Angular Signals
- CRUD operations for infrastructure nodes and edges
- Automatic dirty state tracking and validation triggers

**Data Models**: `src/app/core/models/infra-graph.model.ts`
- Canonical graph representation with nodes and edges
- Type-safe resource definitions for GCP services
- Diagnostic and Terraform generation structures

**Plugin System**: `src/app/infra/plugin-registry.service.ts`
- Registry pattern for managing resource plugins
- Category-based organization of GCP resources
- Dynamic plugin loading and validation

### Configuration Approach

**Build Configuration**: `angular.json`
- Standalone component architecture
- SCSS styling with modular imports
- Development server configuration

**Testing Setup**: `vitest.config.ts`
- Unit testing with Vitest framework
- DOM testing utilities for Angular components

**TypeScript Configuration**: `tsconfig.json`
- Strict type checking
- Modern JavaScript features
- Path mapping for clean imports

### External Dependencies

**Core Framework**: Angular 21 with standalone components and signals
**State Management**: RxJS for reactive streams
**Testing**: Vitest with JSDOM for DOM simulation
**Build Tools**: Angular CLI with modern bundling

### Integration Points

**Canvas Rendering**: SVG-based canvas with panning and zooming
**Drag-and-Drop**: Native HTML5 drag events with custom data transfer
**Code Preview**: Monaco Editor integration for Terraform syntax highlighting
**Persistence**: IndexedDB for local project storage

### Component Relationships

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[App Component] --> B[Top Bar]
    A --> C[Main Area]
    C --> D[Palette]
    C --> E[Canvas]
    C --> F[Inspector]
    A --> G[Bottom Panels]
    G --> H[Diagnostics]
    G --> I[Code Preview]
    
    E --> J[Graph State Service]
    E --> K[Plugin Registry]
    F --> J
    H --> J
    I --> J
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview

**Visual Infrastructure Design**: `src/app/canvas/canvas.component.ts`
- Drag-and-drop resource placement with visual feedback
- Interactive node manipulation with position tracking
- Edge drawing with automatic dependency inference

**Schema-Driven Forms**: `src/app/inspector/inspector.component.ts`
- Dynamic form generation from resource schemas
- Real-time validation with contextual error messages
- Property editing with type safety

**Real-Time Validation**: `src/app/validation/validation.service.ts`
- Schema validation for required fields and types
- Graph integrity checks for dependencies and cycles
- Policy-based warnings for security and cost considerations

**Terraform Generation**: `src/app/terraform-engine/terraform-generator.service.ts`
- AST-based code generation for deterministic output
- Provider configuration and variable management
- Multi-file output with README documentation

### Implementation Highlights

**Plugin Architecture**: `src/app/infra/plugins/`
- Modular resource plugins for extensibility
- Consistent validation and generation interfaces
- Category-based resource organization

**Storage Management**: `src/app/storage/storage.service.ts`
- IndexedDB integration for offline persistence
- Project serialization with metadata tracking
- Import/export functionality for project portability

**Graph Intelligence**: `src/app/graph-engine/graph-engine.service.ts`
- Topological sorting for dependency resolution
- Cycle detection for graph integrity
- Stable ordering for deterministic code generation

### Feature Architecture

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> EmptyCanvas
    EmptyCanvas --> ResourceAdded: Drag resource
    ResourceAdded --> EdgeDrawing: Click node
    EdgeDrawing --> EdgeComplete: Click target node
    EdgeComplete --> Validated: Validate graph
    Validated --> CodeGenerated: Generate Terraform
    CodeGenerated --> ReadyToExport: Review output
    ReadyToExport --> [*]: Export project
    
    Validated --> ResourceAdded: Fix validation errors
    CodeGenerated --> ResourceAdded: Modify resources
```

The application provides a comprehensive solution for visual infrastructure design, combining intuitive user interaction with robust backend processing to deliver professional-grade Terraform configurations that maintain the flexibility for expert customization while significantly lowering the barrier to entry for cloud infrastructure management.

**Sources:**
- [package.json](package.json)
- [angular.json](angular.json)
- [main.ts](src/main.ts)
- [app.component.ts](src/app/layout/app.component.ts)
- [graph-state.service.ts](src/app/core/services/graph-state.service.ts)
- [infra-graph.model.ts](src/app/core/models/infra-graph.model.ts)
- [plugin-registry.service.ts](src/app/infra/plugin-registry.service.ts)
- [terraform-generator.service.ts](src/app/terraform-engine/terraform-generator.service.ts)
- [validation.service.ts](src/app/validation/validation.service.ts)
- [SYSTEM_DESIGN.md](SYSTEM_DESIGN.md)
- [app.component.html](src/app/layout/app.component.html)
- [canvas.component.ts](src/app/canvas/canvas.component.ts)
- [compute-network.plugin.ts](src/app/infra/plugins/compute-network.plugin.ts)
- [storage.service.ts](src/app/storage/storage.service.ts)

</blog>
